# Son of Anton — example environment variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values.

# Telegram notifications (optional)
# When set, the orchestrator sends milestone updates (ticket started, PR opened,
# review recorded, ticket completed, run blocked) to this Telegram chat.
# If either var is absent, the notifier is disabled and delivery continues normally.
#
# Get TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: create a bot via @BotFather on Telegram.
# Get TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID: send a message to your bot, then call
#   https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/getUpdates
#   and read the `chat.id` field from the response.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=

# Discord notifications (optional)
# When set, the orchestrator posts the same milestone updates to this Discord
# channel via webhook. Standalone AI-review PR references render as Markdown
# links; other milestone events post a plain PR URL. Link previews are
# suppressed and mentions are never parsed.
# Precedence: if the Telegram vars above are both set, Telegram wins and this is
# ignored. Discord is used only when Telegram is not fully configured.
#
# Get DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL: in a Discord channel you manage, open
#   Edit Channel → Integrations → Webhooks → New Webhook → Copy Webhook URL.
#   It looks like https://discord.com/api/webhooks/<id>/<token>.
DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=
